Date: Sun 2 Dec 2001
From: Kimberly Kay Mcdonald <kim-chip@eudoramail.com>

A Correction: USAMRIID is the Address for Bioagent Information
---------------------------------------------------------------
The correct Army resource for smallpox information, and other bioagents is
USAMRIID (US Army Medical Research Institute for Infectious Disease).
USAMRCID deals primarily with chemical agents. However, the email address
(<http://ccc.apgea.army.mil>), which Maj. Bruce provided in the ProMED-mail
post Smallpox, bioterrorism response plan - USA (04) 20011130.2920, does
provide a link to USAMRIID.
--
Kimberly McDonald, MD, MPH
LCDR, MC, USNR
Navy Environmental and Preventive Medicine Unit No.2
Norfolk, VA
<kim-chip@eudoramail.com>
